<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-missing-head-in-printed-volume">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Funchal,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 1, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Most Excellent Sir:</hi> I have the honor of
                            informing your excellency that the American steamer Florida left the
                            port last night, about 8.30 p. m., having received the provisions and
                            water which she desired, and the twenty tons of coals which your
                            excellency permitted her to take.</p>
                        <p>God preserve your excellency.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JOAQUIN PEDRO DE CASTELBRANCO, <hi rend="italic">Post Captain R.
                                    N., and Captain of the Port.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">Don Jacintho Antonio
                                    Perdigao</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Civil Governor of the District
                                    of Funchal.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>